# ERROR DEMO — one statement per line.
# Leftover tokens after a complete statement used to silently run as a
# SECOND statement (`x is 2 x is 3` set x to 3; a typo'd `throw "boom"`
# missing `of` silently dropped the raise). Now a parse error (#326).
# expect-error: unexpected identifier after statement ('x') — one statement per line
x is 2 x is 3
print of (str of x)
